# European Option Pricing in Heston Model

**Abstract**  
In this project, we consider four Monte Carlo simulation methods for European option pricing in Heston Model.


Heston model  
Monte Carlo simulation


## Introduction

Black-Scholes Model but it assumes constant variance of the , which is
not realistic in practical stock markets. Heston model assumes
stochastic $v_t$ follows Cox, Ingersoll and Ross(1985) process.

$$
\begin{aligned} d S_{t} &=\mu S_{t} d t+\sqrt{v_{t}} S_{t} d W_{1, t} \\ d v_{t} &=\kappa\left(\theta-v_{t}\right) d t+\sigma \sqrt{v_{t}} d W_{2, t} \end{aligned}
$$




